Create a new virtualenv.

Usage:
    vb new <virtualenv> [OPTIONS]

Options:
    -p python_executable  Executable to use.
    -r requirements file  Specify a requirements file of dependencies to install.
    -v, --verbose         Increase verbosity.
    -q, --quiet           Decrease verbosity.

Create a new virtualenv with the specified name.
The default python used by virtualb can be specified
by setting the $VIRTUALB_DEFAULT_PYTHON, otherwise
the system default will be used.

You can use -r to also specify a requirements
file of packages to install after creating the environment.

Most options will be passed directly to virtualenv,
se virtualenv --help to get more information
about other available options.

